Interface PriorityQueue

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConsPQ, EmptyPQ
    public interface PriorityQueue
    Represents an immutable Priority Queue

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Static Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      PriorityQueue add​(java.lang.Integer priority, java.lang.String value)
      Adds the given element (the priority and its associated value) to the PQ
      static PriorityQueue createEmpty()
      Creates and returns an empty PQ
      java.lang.Boolean isEmpty()
      Checks if PQ is empty
      java.lang.String peek()
      Returns the value in the PQ that has the highest priority, only return one value when multiple elements have the highest priority
      PriorityQueue pop()
      Returns a copy of the PQ without the element with the highest priority, only remove one element when multiple elements have the highest priority
